        "Yaqeen's strength lies in its ability to combine academic rigor with modern accessibility. The organization maintains <cite id=\"12\">12.0 months of working capital</cite>, ensuring long-term operational resilience. Its governance is supported by a <cite id=\"13\">13-member board of directors</cite>, and it has received a <cite id=\"14\">perfect 100 score for Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator. This stability allows the institute to focus on its core mission of producing <cite id=\"15\">well-researched Islamic books and ebooks</cite> that address complex theological and social issues."
      ],
      "summary": "Yaqeen Research Institute Inc is a leading intellectual hub dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">addressing contemporary challenges through high-quality Islamic research</cite> and educational resources. Operating as a global non-profit, the organization focuses on <cite id=\"2\">reviving the essence of Islamic orthodoxy</cite> by providing practical solutions to modern problems. In the 2023 fiscal year, the institute reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $8,759,241</cite>, primarily driven by <cite id=\"4\">$8,744,114 in public contributions</cite>. The organization maintains an exceptionally lean financial model, reporting a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 86.1%</cite> and a <cite id=\"6\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>. Beyond its financial efficiency, Yaqeen has achieved massive digital scale, reaching <cite id=\"7\">100 million total views across its platforms</cite> and supporting <cite id=\"8\">37,075 students through its specialized curriculum</cite>. The institute's work spans research papers, videos, infographics, and podcasts, all designed to <cite id=\"9\">dismantle doubts and nurture conviction</cite> within the Muslim community and beyond.",
